==English==

===Phrase===

'''pleating to the stripe'''

[[Image:Kilt_pleats_002.jpg|thumb|right|175px|Pipe band with kilts pleated to the stripe (military pleating)]]

# A system of pleating a [[kilt]] in which a particular vertical stripe of the [[tartan]] pattern is selected and the [[pleat]]s are arranged so that this chosen stripe runs down the center of each pleat. Also called military pleating. Cp: [[pleating to the sett]]

===Reference===

# Barbara Tewksbury and Elsie Stuehmeyer, ''The Art of Kiltmaking'' (Celtic Dragon Press, Deansboro, NY, 2001, ISBN 0-9703751-0-7)

